    <h1 class="text-center m-4">ALL DIET PLANS</h1>
    <div class="container p-4">
        <h4>Strength Training Diet Plan</h4>
        <hr />
        <p>The goal here is to support muscle growth and repair with a high-protein, moderate-carb diet.</p>
        <h5>Pre-Workout Meal</h5>
        <ul>
            <li class="p-1">
                <strong>1-2 hours before:</strong> Whole-grain toast with avocado and a boiled egg, or Greek yogurt with berries and a handful of oats
            </li>
            <li class="p-1"><strong>Hydration:</strong> Drink 1-2 cups of water</li>
        </ul>
        <h5>Post-Workout Meal</h5>
        <ul>
            <li class="p-1">
                <strong>Within 30 minutes:</strong> Protein shake (whey or plant-based) with a banana
            </li>
            <li class="p-1">
                <strong>Meal:</strong> Grilled chicken breast, sweet potato, and steamed broccoli
            </li>
        </ul>
        <h5>Daily Meals</h5>
        <ol>
            <li class="p-1">
                <strong>Breakfast:</strong> Omelette with veggies (spinach, bell peppers) and whole-grain toast, or a smoothie with banana, spinach, protein powder, and almond milk
            </li>
            <li class="p-1">
                <strong>Lunch:</strong> Quinoa or brown rice with lean protein (chicken or turkey), mixed greens, and olive oil drizzle
            </li>
            <li class="p-1">
                <strong>Dinner:</strong> Salmon with a side of roasted vegetables and quinoa
            </li>
            <li class="p-1">
                <strong>Snacks:</strong> Cottage cheese with fruit, or handful of nuts
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>
    <hr />
    <div class="container p-4">
        <h4>Endurance Training Diet Plan</h4>
        <hr />
        <p>Endurance training requires more carbs to sustain long periods of exercise and a balanced intake of protein and fats.</p>
        <h5>Pre-Workout Meal</h5>
        <ul>
            <li class="p-1">
                <strong>1-2 hours before:</strong> Oatmeal with banana, honey, and a small handful of nuts
            </li>
            <li class="p-1"><strong>Hydration:</strong> Electrolyte drink or water</li>
        </ul>
        <h5>Post-Workout Meal</h5>
        <ul>
            <li class="p-1">
                <strong>Within 30 minutes:</strong> Protein shake (whey or plant-based) with a banana
            </li>
            <li class="p-1">
                <strong>Meal:</strong> Brown rice, black beans, mixed vegetables, and grilled chicken or tofu
            </li>
        </ul>
        <h5>Daily Meals</h5>
        <ol>
            <li class="p-1">
                <strong>Breakfast:</strong> Whole-grain cereal with milk or almond milk, topped with berries and chia seeds
            </li>
            <li class="p-1">
                <strong>Lunch:</strong> Whole-grain wrap with hummus, turkey, lettuce, and bell peppers
            </li>
            <li class="p-1">
                <strong>Dinner:</strong> Pasta with marinara sauce, grilled chicken or chickpeas, and side salad
            </li>
            <li class="p-1">
                <strong>Snacks:</strong> Greek yogurt with honey and almonds, or apple with peanut butter
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>
    <hr />
    <div class="container p-4">
        <h4>Cardio Training Diet Plan</h4>
        <hr />
        <p>Cardio training relies on quick-digesting carbs for immediate energy with a balanced amount of protein to support recovery.</p>
        <h5>Pre-Workout Meal</h5>
        <ul>
            <li class="p-1">
                <strong>1-2 hours before:</strong> Whole-grain toast with almond butter and banana slices
            </li>
            <li class="p-1">
                <strong>Hydration:</strong> Water with a pinch of salt or an electrolyte drink
                </li>
        </ul>
        <h5>Post-Workout Meal</h5>
        <ul>
            <li class="p-1">
                <strong>Within 30 minutes:</strong> Smoothie with banana, protein powder, and almond milk
            </li>
            <li class="p-1">
                <strong>Meal:</strong> Chicken breast, baked potato, and a side of leafy greens
            </li>
        </ul>
        <h5>Daily Meals</h5>
        <ol>
            <li class="p-1">
                <strong>Breakfast:</strong> Greek yogurt with granola and blueberries, or a smoothie bowl with mixed fruit and chia seeds
            </li>
            <li class="p-1">
                <strong>Lunch:</strong> Sandwich on whole-grain bread with lean protein (chicken/turkey) and vegetables, with a side of fruit
            </li>
            <li class="p-1">
                <strong>Dinner:</strong> Stir-fried tofu or lean meat with mixed vegetables and a small portion of rice
            </li>
            <li class="p-1">
                <strong>Snacks:</strong> Trail mix (nuts and dried fruit) or a protein bar
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>
